IMO this could cause a potential problem, `pl` variable is a loop pointer and could be captured by the goroutines in `ParallelizedUntil` function. I posted a demo which has a similar structure and you could run the code below in https://play.golang.org/p/Jc271gRPfdy to view the problems.

```go
func main() {
	values := []struct {
		i int
	}{
		{
			i: 1,
		},
		{
			i: 2,
		},
	}

	wg := sync.WaitGroup{}
	wg.Add(2)
	for _, value := range values {
		go func() {
			defer wg.Done()
			fmt.Println(value.i)
		}()
	}
	wg.Wait()
}

$ go run prog.go
./prog.go:25:16: loop variable value captured by func literal
Go vet exited.

2
2
```

We could solve this problem with the following pattern:

```go
for i := range f.scorePlugins {
  pl := f.scorePlugins[i]
  // ...
}
```

FYI: [Using goroutines on loop iterator variables](https://github.com/golang/go/wiki/CommonMistakes#using-goroutines-on-loop-iterator-variables)

